title: Australia trying to ‘spread the wealth’ whilst businesses get ‘held back’
description: EQ Economics Managing Director Warren Hogan says Australia is not making “forward-leaning decisions” as a nation.  Mr Hogan told Sky News Australia that businesses are being “held back” as a result of this.  “We’re trying to spread the wealth, we’re trying to tax more and we’re trying to spend more.”

title: ‘Hugely consequential moment’: Pete Hegseth threatens war time powers on AI giant
description: CNN Reporter Clare Duffy says Pete Hegseth’s threat to Anthropic is a “hugely consequential moment”.  The US Secretary of War Pete Hegseth has threatened to invoke wartime powers against AI giant Anthropic.  Ms Duffy told Sky News Australia that if the US uses the Defence Production Act, it will be able to use Anthropic’s technology “however it wants”.

title: China has reacted to a threat on Anthony Albanese’s life
description: A classical Chinese dance group was named in a threat, which led to Prime Minister Anthony Albanese being evacuated from his Canberra home.  SBS reported that a threat to Anthony Albanese said a bomb would be detonated at the lodge if performances of Shen Yun were allowed to continue.  The classical dance group was founded by the religious movement Falun Gong, which is banned in China.

title: Fergie and Andrew used Royal ‘status’ to make ‘as much money as possible’
description: Writer and broadcaster Esther Krakue claims former prince Andrew and Sarah Ferguson used their Royal “status” to make as much money as possible.  “Most people are shocked by the complete lack of judgment that the former prince Andrew and Sarah Ferguson established,” Mr Krakue told Sky News host Chris Kenny.  “It was clear they were in it just to make as much money from their status as Royals as possible.”

title: ‘Protecting criminal illegals’: Trump exposes Democrats’ shameful immigration stance
description: Filmmaker Ami Horowitz claims US President Donald Trump exposed Democrats for “standing up for illegals” over the American people.  “That’s kind of the core problem of the Democratic Party, right? They’re standing up for illegals,” Mr Horowitz told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “They’re literally having people protect criminal illegals.”

title: John Fetterman slams Democrats for ‘yelling, screaming and holdings signs’ during SOTU
description: U.S. Senator John Fetterman was the only respectful Democrat to President Donald Trump during his State of the Union (SOTU) address.  During his SOTU address, the president spoke about America’s achievements and honoured people from Erika Kirk to the USA hockey team.  Despite Trump's historic SOTU address, Democratic politicians behaved poorly towards the President.  The only Democrat who respected Trump was John Fetterman - He slammed his party members on Fox News for displaying appalling behaviour.  Fetterman told Fox News that it was disrespectful for his own party to display  "constant kinds of  yelling, screaming and holding signs" during SOTU.   He said, “I don’t care if it’s a Republican or Democrat, it’s a president.”   “Just don’t do that, respect the office regardless who’s in there.”

title: 'Completely failed': Angus Taylor blasts Labor Party and Chalmers over inflation
description: Opposition Leader Angus Taylor has blasted Labor and Treasurer Jim Chalmers following the latest dire inflation data.  "The treasurer has got it wrong all along," Mr Taylor said.  "I've said for years that he keeps putting band aids on bullet wounds, and this is what happens if you don't solve the underlying problem.  "This government has completely failed to beat inflation."

title: ‘CCP-affiliated proxies’ behind threats to Anthony Albanese
description: Former DFAT China scholar Andrew Phelan says “CCP-affiliated proxies” are behind the threats to Anthony Albanese.

title: Trump masterfully lures Dems into an ‘own goal’ during State of the Union address
description: Filmmaker Ami Horowitz claims US President Donald Trump masterfully lured the Democrats into an “obvious trap” during his State of the Union address.  “The Democrats could not do it, they had to have an own goal and sit on their hands with that most obvious statement,” Mr Horowitz told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “It was an obvious trap, and they still walked into it.”

title: Trump hilariously mocks Ilhan Omar after her unhinged outburst at the State of the Union
description: Donald Trump has hilariously mocked Democrat Ilhan Omar after she embarrassed herself with an unhinged outburst during the President’s State of the Union address when he spoke about illegal immigration.

title: ‘I certainly apologise’: Albanese on labelling Grace Tame ‘difficult’
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese weighs in on recent comments he made about former Australian of the Year Grace Tame.  “If there was any misinterpretation, then I certainly apologise,” Mr Albanese said.   “I think that Grace Tame has taken what is personal trauma … and channelled that into helping, in particular, other young women.”

title: ‘Backwards communist policies’: Worrying footage of homeless woman shows 'damage' done to Portland
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has reacted to worrying footage of a homeless woman reacting badly to someone trying to help in the "lefty heartland" of Portland.

title: Nancy Pelosi melts down over Trump’s State of the Union speech on CNN
description: Democrat Congresswoman Nancy Pelosi has melted down on CNN over US President Donald Trump’s State of the Union address.  Pelosi lambasted the president for not spending even “a sentence and a half” on the Ukraine war.  She began her remarks by calling Trump’s speech “lazy” and criticising his Big, Beautiful Bill.  “I thought the speech was lazy ... he started off with BBB, his Big, Beautiful Bill, which is of course disgusting and ugly,” Ms Pelosi said.  The California Democrat was spotted during the State of the Union appearing dazed and sleepy.

title: Donald Trump ‘putting everything in place’ to strike Iran
description: ASPI Resident Senior Fellow David Wroe says US President Donald Trump is “putting everything in place” to strike Iran.  Mr Wroe told Sky News Australia that Donald Trump will “take action” if he needs to.  “What’s got observers concerned here is that it’s unclear what Trump’s objective is.”

title: Royal Family ‘cannot protect’ ex-prince Andrew over ‘deep’ Epstein relationship
description: Writer and broadcaster Esther Krakue discusses the Royal Family cooperating with police over Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor's arrest.  “Prince Andrew has effectively been told by the Royal Family that you now belong to the police,” Ms Krakue told Sky News host Chris Kenny.  “From what the public have seen so far is very suggestive that he had a very tight and deep relationship with Jeffrey Epstein.  “The Royal Family is really cooperating with police, as you would expect them to, and they’ve basically said, we cannot protect this man.”   The former Duke of York is under investigation on suspicion of misconduct in public office and has denied any wrongdoing.
